Project Title: Static Website Hosting on Amazon S3

Objective: To deploy a static website on Amazon S3 with custom domain integration and HTTPS support.

Technologies Used:

Amazon S3
Amazon CloudFront
AWS Certificate Manager (ACM)
Amazon Route 53
Description:

Deployed a fully functional static website using Amazon S3 as the hosting service, ensuring high availability and low-latency access for users.

Key Responsibilities:

Website Hosting on S3:

Configured an Amazon S3 bucket to host a static website, uploading HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files.
Enabled website hosting features on the S3 bucket, including setting the index and error documents for the site.
Custom Domain and DNS Management:

Integrated the website with a custom domain using Amazon Route 53, managing DNS records for domain routing.
Configured Route 53 hosted zones to point the domain to the S3 bucket endpoint.
Content Delivery and Security:

Set up Amazon CloudFront as a Content Delivery Network (CDN) to distribute website content globally, reducing latency and improving load times.
Used AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) to issue an SSL/TLS certificate for the custom domain, enabling HTTPS for secure data transmission.
Performance Optimization:

Configured CloudFront caching policies to optimize content delivery and reduce server load.
Implemented versioning in S3 to manage updates and rollbacks efficiently.
Monitoring and Maintenance:

Enabled S3 bucket logging to track access requests and monitor website traffic.
Used CloudFront monitoring tools to track website performance and user access patterns.
Outcome:

Successfully launched a static website on Amazon S3, providing a fast, reliable, and secure online presence. The project demonstrated expertise in cloud-based web hosting, DNS management, and content delivery optimization.
